00:25:18,080 --> 00:25:19,536
That kind of mirrors
what happened to him

593
00:25:19,560 --> 00:25:20,926
when he was little.

594
00:25:20,950 --> 00:25:23,706
Yeah, look, the police bombed
MOVE headquarters.

595
00:25:23,730 --> 00:25:25,316
Gerry loses his childhood home.

596
00:25:25,340 --> 00:25:26,756
Then he loses his family.

597
00:25:26,780 --> 00:25:29,456
So it's happening again
to him 40 years later.

598
00:25:29,480 --> 00:25:31,066
That must be what triggered him.

599
00:25:31,090 --> 00:25:32,586
<i>After his house was foreclosed,</i>

600
00:25:32,610 --> 00:25:33,766
Gerry stayed at a men's shelter.

601
00:25:33,790 --> 00:25:35,246
We just spoke to the director.

602
00:25:35,270 --> 00:25:36,766
Yeah, you think he's going
after the shelter next?

603
00:25:36,790 --> 00:25:38,076
<i>They've been alerted.</i>

604
00:25:38,100 --> 00:25:39,556
Gerry even brought his
kids there and pretended

605
00:25:39,580 --> 00:25:41,076
it was a weekend excursion.

606
00:25:41,100 --> 00:25:43,426
The shelter has a strict no-kids policy,

607
00:25:43,450 --> 00:25:44,686
so they had to ask Gerry to leave.

608
00:25:44,710 --> 00:25:46,686
And he hasn't been back since.

609
00:25:46,710 --> 00:25:49,386
That's harsh.

610
00:25:49,410 --> 00:25:50,436
All right.

611
00:25:50,460 --> 00:25:52,736
So no family, no home.

612
00:25:52,760 --> 00:25:54,476
This guy's got nothing to lose.

613
00:25:54,500 --> 00:25:55,916
Where's he going next?

614
00:25:55,940 --> 00:25:57,566
The shelter director
said that Gerry was friendly

615
00:25:57,590 --> 00:25:59,176
with a guy named Trent
who comes around

616
00:25:59,200 --> 00:26:01,316
for a hot meal, but also keeps a spot

617
00:26:01,340 --> 00:26:03,186
at an encampment in Astoria.

618
00:26:03,210 --> 00:26:04,536
Sending you the cross streets.

619
00:26:04,560 --> 00:26:05,886
Meet us there.

620
00:26:05,910 --> 00:26:07,870
All right.

621
00:26:10,610 --> 00:26:11,587
Hana.

622
00:26:11,611 --> 00:26:13,286
Ethan's calling you.

623
00:26:13,310 --> 00:26:14,830
Here.

624
00:26:18,440 --> 00:26:19,856
You're not going to answer it?

625
00:26:19,880 --> 00:26:20,946
Nope.

626
00:26:20,970 --> 00:26:22,596
We broke up two weeks ago.

627
00:26:22,620 --> 00:26:25,296
Hana, I'm so sorry.

628
00:26:25,320 --> 00:26:26,556
There were signs.

629
00:26:26,580 --> 00:26:28,516
- I missed them.
- What kind of signs?

630
00:26:28,540 --> 00:26:29,476
I don't want to talk about it.

631
00:26:29,500 --> 00:26:31,630
Yeah, of course.

632
00:26:34,020 --> 00:26:35,680
<i>Have you seen this guy?</i>

633
00:26:37,550 --> 00:26:38,956
Have you seen this man?

634
00:26:38,980 --> 00:26:40,616
OK. Thank you.

635
00:26:40,640 --> 00:26:41,786
Nobody recognizes him.

636
00:26:41,810 --> 00:26:42,876
At least that's what they say.

637
00:26:42,900 --> 00:26:44,316
Half of them won't even talk.

638
00:26:44,340 --> 00:26:45,746
They don't trust the badge.

639
00:26:45,770 --> 00:26:47,186
I mean, every major city,
cops are constantly

640
00:26:47,210 --> 00:26:48,756
harassing them,
making them move around,

641
00:26:48,780 --> 00:26:50,236
set up camps in different places.

642
00:26:50,260 --> 00:26:51,716
That's why MOVE didn't trust the cops

643
00:26:51,740 --> 00:26:53,716
the constant harassment.

644
00:26:53,740 --> 00:26:55,236
It's Horus, Gerry's old boss.

645
00:26:55,260 --> 00:26:56,806
All right.

646
00:26:56,830 --> 00:26:58,416
Remy's found Trent.

647
00:26:58,440 --> 00:27:00,416
Great.

648
00:27:00,440 --> 00:27:02,376
How well do you know Gerry?

649
00:27:02,400 --> 00:27:03,986
You know, about as well as

650
00:27:04,010 --> 00:27:05,726
you get to know the guy
who's stuck in the same

651
00:27:05,750 --> 00:27:07,270
sinking boat with you.

652
00:27:09,320 --> 00:27:10,686
It must be pretty hard

653
00:27:10,710 --> 00:27:12,426
to get a decent night's
sleep around here.

654
00:27:12,450 --> 00:27:13,776
Why do you stay?

655
00:27:13,800 --> 00:27:15,426
Yeah, it's just noise, you know.

656
00:27:15,450 --> 00:27:16,606
Better than camping out someplace

657
00:27:16,630 --> 00:27:18,306
quiet and residential.

658
00:27:18,330 --> 00:27:21,006
And you always got
the cops on your ass.

659
00:27:21,030 --> 00:27:24,006
OK, so you're here because
the neighbors don't complain.

660
00:27:24,030 --> 00:27:26,706
Out of sight, out of mind, which is exactly

661
00:27:26,730 --> 00:27:28,836
how the public likes
their homeless, right?

662
00:27:28,860 --> 00:27:32,316
I'm sorry, the unhoused,
as though semantics

663
00:27:32,340 --> 00:27:34,796
are going to put a freaking
roof over our heads.

664
00:27:34,820 --> 00:27:37,066
Is that what you and Gerry talked about?

665
00:27:37,090 --> 00:27:40,156
Yeah, I mean, I'm over it, man.

666
00:27:40,180 --> 00:27:42,976
But Gerry...

667
00:27:43,000 --> 00:27:46,026
He would get all riled up.

668
00:27:46,050 --> 00:27:48,896
He talks about how
the police and politicians,

669
00:27:48,920 --> 00:27:51,776
they don't want to do their
jobs, yada, yada, you know.

670
00:27:51,800 --> 00:27:53,116
You talking about the housing crisis?

671
00:27:53,140 --> 00:27:55,556
I'm talking about any crisis, man.

672
00:27:55,580 --> 00:27:56,866
Not like we elected them to put out

673
00:27:56,890 --> 00:27:58,386
these kind of fires or anything.

674
00:27:58,410 --> 00:28:01,256
Though, if you ask Gerry,

675
00:28:01,280 --> 00:28:03,176
he'd say they wouldn't put out a fire

676
00:28:03,200 --> 00:28:06,436
even if that was exactly their job.

677
00:28:06,460 --> 00:28:08,266
What do you mean by that?

678
00:28:08,290 --> 00:28:10,136
His house burned down
when he was a kid.

679
00:28:10,160 --> 00:28:12,576
He said the firefighters, they showed up.

680
00:28:12,600 --> 00:28:14,226
They just stood around

681
00:28:14,250 --> 00:28:16,950
and watched that baby
burn to the ground.

682
00:28:19,820 --> 00:28:21,716
So that was Gerry's old boss.

683
00:28:21,740 --> 00:28:23,936
He said all of the Tovarc is accounted for.

684
00:28:23,960 --> 00:28:26,896
However, a spool of det cord
went missing in the last day.

685
00:28:26,920 --> 00:28:29,066
They never changed the locks
after Gerry got fired,

686
00:28:29,090 --> 00:28:31,596
so he could have used his key to steal it.

687
00:28:31,620 --> 00:28:33,206
What's det cord?

688
00:28:33,230 --> 00:28:34,636
It's a detonation cord.

689
00:28:34,660 --> 00:28:36,296
Yeah, that's - it's a tiny little tube

690
00:28:36,320 --> 00:28:37,946
filled with explosives.

691
00:28:37,970 --> 00:28:39,426
We used to use that back in Afghan

692
00:28:39,450 --> 00:28:40,736
to blow up expired ordnance.

693
00:28:40,760 --> 00:28:42,086
The arson investigator said that Tovarc

694
00:28:42,110 --> 00:28:44,606
needs a secondary explosive
to be triggered.

695
00:28:44,630 --> 00:28:45,916
Would det cord work?

696
00:28:45,940 --> 00:28:47,916
It's exactly what det cord's for.

697
00:28:47,940 --> 00:28:50,746
Turn a little kaboom into a big kaboom.

698
00:28:50,770 --> 00:28:52,046
No big deal.

699
00:28:52,070 --> 00:28:53,966
That whole blast you heard earlier

700
00:28:53,990 --> 00:28:55,356
I mean, you got those
construction crews.

701
00:28:55,380 --> 00:28:58,730
They're running det cord
and Tovarc every damn day.

702
00:29:00,600 --> 00:29:01,926
OK.

703
00:29:01,950 --> 00:29:03,756
So Gerry could have gotten
the Tovarc from anywhere,

704
00:29:03,780 --> 00:29:05,276
including that construction site.

705
00:29:05,300 --> 00:29:07,366
Yeah, but he didn't know
he needed the det cord

706
00:29:07,390 --> 00:29:08,766
to make it explode.

707
00:29:08,790 --> 00:29:10,456
Until he saw the first
two arsons were fires,

708
00:29:10,480 --> 00:29:11,856
not explosions.

709
00:29:11,880 --> 00:29:13,466
Now that he has these two ingredients,

710
00:29:13,490 --> 00:29:16,140
it's only a matter of time
before the big kaboom.

