00:29:24,110 --> 00:29:25,476
You don't understand.

715
00:29:25,500 --> 00:29:26,776
You're asking me about something

716
00:29:26,800 --> 00:29:29,256
that happened 40 years ago.

717
00:29:29,280 --> 00:29:30,656
I don't remember the details.

718
00:29:30,680 --> 00:29:32,136
<i>We're not passing judgment.</i>

719
00:29:32,160 --> 00:29:34,566
We just need to know
what really happened.

720
00:29:34,590 --> 00:29:37,046
It was my second year on the job.

721
00:29:37,070 --> 00:29:38,316
I was following orders.

722
00:29:38,340 --> 00:29:40,056
What were your orders?

723
00:29:40,080 --> 00:29:41,406
<i>To stand down.</i>

724
00:29:41,430 --> 00:29:44,056
No one expected the fire
to get so out of control.

725
00:29:44,080 --> 00:29:45,536
It got out of control

726
00:29:45,560 --> 00:29:47,936
because you didn't do anything to stop it.

727
00:29:47,960 --> 00:29:50,106
It was a mess.

728
00:29:50,130 --> 00:29:52,416
My lieutenant called it a war zone.

729
00:29:52,440 --> 00:29:55,246
<i>And this is the guy that
did two tours in Vietnam.</i>

730
00:29:55,270 --> 00:29:56,806
<i>Bullets were flying.</i>

731
00:29:56,830 --> 00:29:58,076
Who started the shooting?

732
00:29:58,100 --> 00:29:59,596
<i>Depends on who you ask.</i>

733
00:29:59,620 --> 00:30:03,076
Some folks say the cops were
shooting at the MOVE folks

734
00:30:03,100 --> 00:30:04,686
trying to escape the fire.

735
00:30:04,710 --> 00:30:08,606
And the cops say
MOVE fired at them first.

736
00:30:08,630 --> 00:30:11,916
Now, what were we supposed to do?

737
00:30:11,940 --> 00:30:15,436
We couldn't disobey
the fire commissioner.

738
00:30:15,460 --> 00:30:17,266
Is he the one who gave the order?

739
00:30:17,290 --> 00:30:18,396
As far as I know, he was given that order

740
00:30:18,420 --> 00:30:19,770
by the police commissioner.

741
00:30:25,380 --> 00:30:29,056
Is this why my daughter was killed?

742
00:30:29,080 --> 00:30:32,676
Over something I did four decades ago?

743
00:30:32,700 --> 00:30:34,016
No.

744
00:30:34,040 --> 00:30:36,350
It's over what you didn't do.

745
00:30:40,440 --> 00:30:42,286
Gerry went after a firefighter
at the scene

746
00:30:42,310 --> 00:30:43,686
the helicopter pilot
who dropped the bomb,

747
00:30:43,710 --> 00:30:44,986
then the mayor.

748
00:30:45,010 --> 00:30:46,646
He's working his way
up the chain of command.

749
00:30:46,670 --> 00:30:48,206
Contact the fire
and police commissioners.

750
00:30:48,230 --> 00:30:49,516
We got to warn them.

751
00:30:49,540 --> 00:30:51,296
The Philadelphia police
commissioner in 1985

752
00:30:51,320 --> 00:30:52,956
was Victor Kipling.

753
00:30:52,980 --> 00:30:55,346
He lives in a senior community
in New Rochelle.

754
00:30:55,370 --> 00:30:57,176
Fire commissioner is in New York now.

