00:32:49,790 --> 00:32:51,676
but maybe he was going
after Vicki all along.

793
00:32:51,700 --> 00:32:53,946
He didn't mix up Eric Junior, by the way.

794
00:32:53,970 --> 00:32:56,686
He was stalking the mayor's
grandson on purpose.

795
00:32:56,710 --> 00:32:58,556
And Finn Rayson's son
was supposed to be home

796
00:32:58,580 --> 00:33:00,020
when Gerry set that fire.

797
00:33:02,980 --> 00:33:04,346
<i>What's up, Ray?</i>

798
00:33:04,370 --> 00:33:06,086
We got a BOLO hit on
Gerald's car in the Bronx.

799
00:33:06,110 --> 00:33:07,126
We're headed there now.

800
00:33:07,150 --> 00:33:08,680
I'll drop you a location pin.

801
00:33:11,110 --> 00:33:13,786
Bring around the Tahoe.

802
00:33:13,810 --> 00:33:15,926
Isn't that where
the fire commissioner lives?

803
00:33:15,950 --> 00:33:17,096
House sitter said he's out of town.

804
00:33:17,120 --> 00:33:18,706
He and his wife are in Florida.

805
00:33:18,730 --> 00:33:20,666
Does he have relatives in the Bronx?

806
00:33:20,690 --> 00:33:22,576
We think Gerry's going
after the family members

807
00:33:22,600 --> 00:33:24,586
of the people responsible
for the bombing.

808
00:33:24,610 --> 00:33:26,886
His car is parked in
a dense residential area.

809
00:33:26,910 --> 00:33:28,546
If we have to account for relatives,

810
00:33:28,570 --> 00:33:30,480
it will take time
to figure out who he's after.

811
00:33:33,700 --> 00:33:37,376
They found our fugitive's
car in the Bronx.

812
00:33:37,400 --> 00:33:39,246
Where in the Bronx?

813
00:33:39,270 --> 00:33:42,320
My granddaughter lives there.

814
00:33:58,160 --> 00:33:59,746
Maya Kipling?

815
00:33:59,770 --> 00:34:02,380
FBI.

816
00:34:03,250 --> 00:34:04,366
Can I help you?

817
00:34:04,390 --> 00:34:06,690
I'm Special Agent Remy Scott.

818
00:34:08,820 --> 00:34:10,326
Is somebody already in there?

819
00:34:10,350 --> 00:34:11,496
We're fine.

820
00:34:11,520 --> 00:34:12,896
It's all we have, Billy.

821
00:34:12,920 --> 00:34:14,506
Let's go upstairs.

822
00:34:14,530 --> 00:34:17,180
Are there kids in there?

823
00:34:19,360 --> 00:34:21,050
We think you might be in danger.

824
00:34:30,240 --> 00:34:31,696
This is my cousin Terry.

825
00:34:31,720 --> 00:34:33,086
She helps me out sometimes.

826
00:34:33,110 --> 00:34:34,346
Helps you out with what?

827
00:34:34,370 --> 00:34:35,656
Are you running
a daycare from your house?

828
00:34:35,680 --> 00:34:37,006
I'm going to get a license.

829
00:34:37,030 --> 00:34:38,176
I just haven't gotten around to it yet.

830
00:34:38,200 --> 00:34:39,306
We're the FBI, not the IRS.

831
00:34:39,330 --> 00:34:40,307
We don't care about that.

832
00:34:40,331 --> 00:34:41,916
Are you in trouble?

833
00:34:41,940 --> 00:34:43,056
It's fine.

834
00:34:43,080 --> 00:34:44,536
Go help Angela start quiet hour, OK?

835
00:34:44,560 --> 00:34:47,276
Just let me talk to them.

836
00:34:47,300 --> 00:34:49,106
So what's going on?

837
00:34:49,130 --> 00:34:51,796
A serial arsonist might be
targeting your home.

838
00:34:51,820 --> 00:34:52,846
What?

839
00:34:52,870 --> 00:34:54,066
How many kids do you have here?

840
00:34:54,090 --> 00:34:55,286
We have six today.

841
00:34:55,310 --> 00:34:56,716
Angela and Terry are with them upstairs.

842
00:34:56,740 --> 00:34:58,246
OK. I need you to contact their parents

843
00:34:58,270 --> 00:34:59,636
and have them pick them up now.

844
00:34:59,660 --> 00:35:01,530
- Are you sure?
- Get them out.

845
00:35:16,280 --> 00:35:17,346
Angela?

846
00:35:17,370 --> 00:35:18,566
Angela, bring the kids down. Come on.

847
00:35:18,590 --> 00:35:21,006
Come on. Come on, honey. Yes.

848
00:35:21,030 --> 00:35:22,226
Yeah, come on. Come on.

849
00:35:22,250 --> 00:35:23,526
It's OK. Let's head outside, all right?

850
00:35:23,550 --> 00:35:25,226
We got a fire in here.

851
00:35:25,250 --> 00:35:26,616
- Get them out.
- We're going to head out.

852
00:35:26,640 --> 00:35:27,706
Head out. There's a fire.

853
00:35:27,730 --> 00:35:29,836
Let's go, all right?

854
00:35:29,860 --> 00:35:31,096
Come on, guys, we gotta get out.

855
00:35:31,120 --> 00:35:32,186
Come on, come on.

856
00:35:32,210 --> 00:35:33,536
Keep going down the stairs.

857
00:35:33,560 --> 00:35:35,886
What happened? Whose kids are these?

858
00:35:35,910 --> 00:35:37,586
She runs a daycare in there.
We got to get them out of here.

859
00:35:37,610 --> 00:35:38,587
I got them.

860
00:35:38,611 --> 00:35:41,066
- Come on.
- Where's Terry?

861
00:35:41,090 --> 00:35:42,456
- What?
- I don't know.

862
00:35:42,480 --> 00:35:43,726
- I just grabbed the kids.
- OK.

863
00:35:43,750 --> 00:35:45,066
I got her. Go, go.

864
00:35:45,090 --> 00:35:46,156
- Nina.
- I got her.

865
00:35:46,180 --> 00:35:47,206
We got two inside.

866
00:35:47,230 --> 00:35:48,726
One's an FBI agent.

867
00:35:48,750 --> 00:35:49,750
Fire in the back.

868
00:35:53,450 --> 00:35:55,020
He's on the roof!

869
00:35:57,410 --> 00:35:58,646
Hey.

870
00:35:58,670 --> 00:36:01,566
Hey... Terry.

871
00:36:01,590 --> 00:36:02,696
Terry, wake up.

872
00:36:02,720 --> 00:36:03,746
Come on.

873
00:36:03,770 --> 00:36:05,136
Come on.

874
00:36:05,160 --> 00:36:07,046
I'm going to get you out of here.

875
00:36:07,070 --> 00:36:08,070
Get down!

876
00:36:25,050 --> 00:36:27,196
Guys, where is he?

877
00:36:27,220 --> 00:36:28,660
<i>Across the street on the roof.</i>

878
00:36:30,440 --> 00:36:31,596
Cover us.

879
00:36:31,620 --> 00:36:33,190
OK.

880
00:36:36,010 --> 00:36:36,947
Stay with me.

881
00:36:36,971 --> 00:36:38,426
I'm right here.

882
00:36:38,450 --> 00:36:39,890
Cover your mouth. Cover your mouth.

883
00:36:40,980 --> 00:36:44,020
Guys, we gotta get out of here.

884
00:36:50,330 --> 00:36:52,160
They're firing at us!

885
00:36:56,770 --> 00:36:59,236
You guys go that way. I'll circle around.

886
00:36:59,260 --> 00:37:00,576
Nina, you're clear.

887
00:37:00,600 --> 00:37:01,586
<i>Get out of there.</i>

888
00:37:01,610 --> 00:37:03,886
Come on, come on.

889
00:37:03,910 --> 00:37:05,130
Come on.

890
00:37:10,570 --> 00:37:12,596
Come on. Come on, come on, come on.

891
00:37:12,620 --> 00:37:14,506
I got you. I got you.

892
00:37:14,530 --> 00:37:17,270
We need help... medical assistance!

893
00:37:23,150 --> 00:37:24,646
FBI.

894
00:37:24,670 --> 00:37:26,956
You're stuck between a rock
and a hard place, Gerry.

895
00:37:26,980 --> 00:37:28,436
How does it feel?

896
00:37:28,460 --> 00:37:30,216
Like any other day in the life.

897
00:37:30,240 --> 00:37:31,916
We don't want to shoot you, Gerry.

898
00:37:31,940 --> 00:37:32,956
Don't give us a reason to.

899
00:37:32,980 --> 00:37:34,176
Put the gun down.

900
00:37:34,200 --> 00:37:35,356
Enough people have been hurt.

901
00:37:35,380 --> 00:37:37,666
All right? This ain't '85 back in Philly.

902
00:37:37,690 --> 00:37:39,616
They took a lot from you.

903
00:37:39,640 --> 00:37:40,617
Never made things right.

904
00:37:40,641 --> 00:37:41,966
They never do.

905
00:37:41,990 --> 00:37:44,496
But you can make things
right for your kids now.

906
00:37:44,520 --> 00:37:47,016
Do you have any idea how it feels

907
00:37:47,040 --> 00:37:49,806
not being able to give them
a home, keep them safe,

908
00:37:49,830 --> 00:37:51,416
keep our family together?

909
00:37:51,440 --> 00:37:54,936
No, but I know four walls
and a roof don't make a home.

910
00:37:54,960 --> 00:37:56,156
Showing up for them does.

911
00:37:56,180 --> 00:37:57,896
I did everything for my family!

912
00:37:57,920 --> 00:38:00,036
That doesn't concern me.

913
00:38:00,060 --> 00:38:01,516
Drop your weapon.

914
00:38:01,540 --> 00:38:04,036
And then what?

915
00:38:04,060 --> 00:38:06,280
I'm drowning, man.

916
00:38:08,890 --> 00:38:11,996
All my life has been
one thing after the other,

917
00:38:12,020 --> 00:38:14,086
like everyone is at the pool party,

918
00:38:14,110 --> 00:38:16,306
and I'm underwater in the deep end.

919
00:38:16,330 --> 00:38:19,290
And by the time anyone thinks of me,

920
00:38:21,210 --> 00:38:22,966
I'll be nothing but an air bubble.

921
00:38:22,990 --> 00:38:26,706
You got our attention.

922
00:38:26,730 --> 00:38:30,536
But you got to think about your kids.

923
00:38:30,560 --> 00:38:32,066
I don't want to have to explain to them

924
00:38:32,090 --> 00:38:34,310
why my partner shot you.

925
00:38:40,920 --> 00:38:42,246
Come on, Gerry.

926
00:38:42,270 --> 00:38:44,076
Break the cycle.

927
00:38:44,100 --> 00:38:47,336
Put the gun down.

928
00:38:47,360 --> 00:38:48,906
Man, I'm not letting you go out like this.

929
00:38:48,930 --> 00:38:51,190
Put the gun down.

930
00:39:05,510 --> 00:39:06,796
Hands behind your head.

931
00:39:06,820 --> 00:39:08,780
Let's go.

932
00:39:30,620 --> 00:39:32,296
Thank you for staying so late.

933
00:39:32,320 --> 00:39:33,297
I appreciate it.

934
00:39:33,321 --> 00:39:34,426
Of course.

935
00:39:34,450 --> 00:39:35,776
Dougie's an easy-going kid.

936
00:39:35,800 --> 00:39:37,476
Yeah, he gets that one from his dad.

937
00:39:37,500 --> 00:39:39,810
- Good night.
- Night.

938
00:39:52,390 --> 00:39:54,056
Hi. How'd it go with Brett?

939
00:39:54,080 --> 00:39:55,756
<i>Marina... Nina, it's me.</i>

940
00:39:55,780 --> 00:39:58,106
- Dad?
<i>- Listen, don't hang up.</i>

941
00:39:58,130 --> 00:40:00,326
No, you do not get
to call me from Tink's phone.

942
00:40:00,350 --> 00:40:01,766
You want to talk?

943
00:40:01,790 --> 00:40:03,376
<i>Have the balls to call me
from your own phone.</i>

944
00:40:03,400 --> 00:40:06,416
Just listen, please.

945
00:40:06,440 --> 00:40:08,466
I'm at the hospital.

946
00:40:08,490 --> 00:40:10,076
<i>Tink and Brett got into it.</i>

947
00:40:10,100 --> 00:40:12,166
And evidently, he knocked
her around quite a bit.

948
00:40:12,190 --> 00:40:13,556
What? What?

949
00:40:13,580 --> 00:40:15,816
What do you mean
he knocked her around?

950
00:40:15,840 --> 00:40:16,996
He hit her?

951
00:40:17,020 --> 00:40:18,476
How bad is it?

952
00:40:18,500 --> 00:40:20,346
Bad enough that even though

953
00:40:20,370 --> 00:40:23,046
she's not going to press charges,

954
00:40:23,070 --> 00:40:24,476
<i>the boys down at the station</i>

955
00:40:24,500 --> 00:40:26,136
<i>are going to keep him locked up</i>

956
00:40:26,160 --> 00:40:31,446
in the drunk tank overnight
for his own safety.

957
00:40:31,470 --> 00:40:33,666
Yeah, because we're really
concerned with his safety.

958
00:40:33,690 --> 00:40:35,666
Come on.

959
00:40:35,690 --> 00:40:37,276
- Hey, can you stay?
- Yeah.

960
00:40:37,300 --> 00:40:38,586
<i>I always said about Brett,
he's got two brain cells,</i>

961
00:40:38,610 --> 00:40:40,366
<i>and they're both fighting for third place.</i>

962
00:40:40,390 --> 00:40:42,456
A reasonable man would
have gotten a job.

963
00:40:42,480 --> 00:40:44,846
Yeah. Well, he's not reasonable.

964
00:40:44,870 --> 00:40:47,506
I mean, we knew that he was
never going to get a job.

965
00:40:47,530 --> 00:40:49,726
I don't know why I told her to talk to him.

966
00:40:49,750 --> 00:40:51,246
Yeah.

967
00:40:51,270 --> 00:40:52,376
Well, I'm going to give him
a dose of his own medicine

968
00:40:52,400 --> 00:40:53,726
next time I see him.

969
00:40:53,750 --> 00:40:56,206
Yeah, not if I beat you to it.

970
00:40:56,230 --> 00:40:57,776
You're going to need a long reach.

971
00:40:57,800 --> 00:41:00,346
I'm getting on the next flight to Houston.

972
00:41:00,370 --> 00:41:02,060
I'm coming home, Dad.


